            <title>[JCR-2061] JSR 283: References and Dereferencing of Property Values</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-2061</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>References&lt;br/&gt;
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;br/&gt;
new methods are:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
- Node.getReferences(String name) PropertyIterator &lt;br/&gt;
- Node.getWeakReferences() PropertyIterator &lt;br/&gt;
- Node.getWeakReferences(String name) PropertyIterator&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Derferencing&lt;br/&gt;
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;br/&gt;
As of JSR 283 the following property types may be dereferenced to a Node:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
- REFERENCE&lt;br/&gt;
- WEAKREFERENCE&lt;br/&gt;
- PATH&lt;br/&gt;
- any type that can be converted to either of the types above&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The new method&lt;br/&gt;
- Property.getProperty() returns the Property pointed to by a PATH value.&lt;br/&gt;
- any type that can be converted to PATH&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
